---
import LegalPageLayout from "../layouts/LegalPageLayout.astro";

const tocItems = [
  { id: "about-this-policy", label: "1. About this policy" },
  { id: "data-we-collect", label: "2. Personal data we collect" },
  { id: "how-we-use", label: "3. How and why we use it" },
  { id: "who-we-share-with", label: "4. Who we share it with" },
  { id: "international-transfers", label: "5. International transfers" },
  { id: "how-long", label: "6. How long we keep it" },
  { id: "your-rights", label: "7. Your rights" },
  { id: "cookies", label: "8. Cookies" },
  { id: "security-and-limits", label: "9. Security &amp; limits" },
  { id: "ico-complaints", label: "10. Right to complain to the ICO" },
  { id: "changes-to-policy", label: "11. Changes to this policy" },
  { id: "contact-us", label: "12. Contact us" },
];
---

<LegalPageLayout
  metaTitle="ISOv8® | Privacy Policy"
  description="How ISOv8® collects, uses, and protects your personal data when you visit isov8.co.uk or contact us through the website."
  keywords={["ISOv8 privacy policy", "UK GDPR", "data protection", "container conversions privacy"]}
  breadcrumbName="Privacy Policy"
  h1="Privacy Policy"
  publishedDate="28/04/2026"
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <div class="space-y-3">
    <h2 id="about-this-policy" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">1. About this policy</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      This Privacy Policy explains how ISOv8&reg; by ContainerKing&reg; Limited (&ldquo;ISOv8&reg;&rdquo;, &ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;, &ldquo;our&rdquo;) collects, uses, and protects personal data you provide through isov8.co.uk. ContainerKing&reg; Limited is the data controller for that personal data and is registered in England and Wales under company number 03402386 (registered office: Celsius Parc, Cupola Way, Scunthorpe, North Lincolnshire, DN15 9YJ).
    </p>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We comply with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR), the Data Protection Act 2018, and the Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations (PECR). This policy should be read alongside our <a href="/cookie-policy" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">Cookie Policy</a>, which explains the cookies and similar technologies used on the site.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="data-we-collect" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">2. Personal data we collect</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We only collect the personal data we genuinely need to respond to your enquiry and operate the website. Specifically:
    </p>
    <h3 class="mt-10 text-[1.75rem] font-[500] leading-tight text-black">2.1 Information you give us</h3>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      When you submit our enquiry form (the &ldquo;Engage&rdquo; form, also available at <a href="/contact" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">/contact</a>), we collect:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      <li>your <strong>name</strong>;</li>
      <li>your <strong>telephone number</strong>;</li>
      <li>your <strong>business name</strong>; and</li>
      <li>the <strong>enquiry details</strong> you choose to provide (free-text message).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      The form does not ask for an email address. If you choose to include an email address, postal address, or other personal information inside your enquiry message, that information will be processed alongside the rest of your enquiry on the same lawful basis.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      If you call us on <a href="tel:+441724870000" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">01724 870000</a> or email us at <a href="mailto:engage@isov8.co.uk" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">engage@isov8.co.uk</a>, we will also process the contact details you use and the content of your communication.
    </p>
    <h3 class="mt-10 text-[1.75rem] font-[500] leading-tight text-black">2.2 Information collected automatically</h3>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      When you use the site, our hosting provider (Netlify) and, where you have given consent, Google Analytics 4 may receive limited technical information &mdash; such as IP address, approximate location derived from IP, browser type, device type, referring website, and pages visited. This information is described in our <a href="/cookie-policy" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">Cookie Policy</a>. Where used, it is anonymised or pseudonymised wherever practicable.
    </p>
    <h3 class="mt-10 text-[1.75rem] font-[500] leading-tight text-black">2.3 Special category data</h3>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We do not ask for, and do not need, special category personal data (such as health, racial or ethnic origin, religious beliefs, or sexual orientation). Please do not include such information in your enquiry message.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="how-we-use" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">3. How and why we use your personal data</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We only use your personal data for the purposes set out below, and only on a lawful basis recognised under UK GDPR.
    </p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full min-w-[720px] table-fixed border-collapse text-left text-[0.875rem] text-[#4b5563]">
        <colgroup>
          <col style="width: 22%;" />
          <col style="width: 22%;" />
          <col style="width: 18%;" />
          <col style="width: 38%;" />
        </colgroup>
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 text-[#111111]">
            <th class="px-3 py-2 font-[600]">Purpose</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 font-[600]">Personal data used</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 font-[600]">Lawful basis</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 font-[600]">Notes</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Responding to your enquiry and providing a quote or further information</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Name, telephone number, business name, enquiry details</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">UK GDPR Art 6(1)(b) &ndash; taking steps at your request prior to entering into a contract</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Submitting the enquiry form is itself a request for us to take pre-contractual steps. Without these details we cannot reply.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Keeping a record of correspondence where no contract follows</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Name, telephone number, business name, enquiry details</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">UK GDPR Art 6(1)(f) &ndash; legitimate interests</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">We have a legitimate interest in keeping a short record of who has contacted us, what was discussed, and when, so that we can answer follow-up questions and resolve any disputes.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Operating the website securely and reliably</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Technical data (IP address, browser, request logs)</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">UK GDPR Art 6(1)(f) &ndash; legitimate interests</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">We have a legitimate interest in protecting the site against abuse, debugging errors, and ensuring availability.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Measuring how the site is used (analytics)</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Pseudonymous identifiers and engagement data via Google Analytics 4</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">UK GDPR Art 6(1)(a) &ndash; consent</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Loaded only after you grant consent through our cookie banner. You can withdraw consent at any time.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Complying with legal obligations</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Any of the above, where required</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">UK GDPR Art 6(1)(c) &ndash; legal obligation</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Used only when we are required to retain or disclose data by law (e.g. responding to a regulatory or court order).</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We do not use your personal data to send marketing emails, build advertising audiences, profile you, or make automated decisions about you.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="who-we-share-with" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">4. Who we share your personal data with</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We do not sell your personal data, and we do not share it with anyone for their own marketing purposes. We do share limited personal data with the following categories of recipient, only to the extent necessary:
    </p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full min-w-[720px] table-fixed border-collapse text-left text-[0.875rem] text-[#4b5563]">
        <colgroup>
          <col style="width: 22%;" />
          <col style="width: 22%;" />
          <col style="width: 18%;" />
          <col style="width: 38%;" />
        </colgroup>
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 text-[#111111]">
            <th class="px-3 py-2 font-[600]">Recipient</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 font-[600]">Role</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 font-[600]">Location</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 font-[600]">Purpose</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">ISOv8&reg; / ContainerKing&reg; sales team</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Internal recipients (controller)</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">United Kingdom</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Receiving, qualifying, and responding to your enquiry; preparing quotes and project proposals.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Netlify</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Processor &ndash; website hosting and form capture (Netlify Forms, serverless functions)</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">United States, with global edge infrastructure</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Serving the website and receiving form submissions before they are forwarded to our inbox.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Our email and IT service providers</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Processors &ndash; mailbox hosting and IT support</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">United Kingdom / European Economic Area / United States, depending on the provider</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Delivering and storing emails sent to or from engage@isov8.co.uk, and providing technical support. Specific provider names will be made available on request to a data subject.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="break-words border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Google (Google Analytics 4)</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Processor &ndash; website analytics</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">United States, with regional infrastructure</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Used only with your consent. Configured under Google Consent Mode v2 with IP anonymisation where applicable.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="break-words border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Adobe (Adobe Fonts)</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Processor &ndash; font delivery</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">United States / European Economic Area</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Receives technical request information (such as IP address) needed to deliver fonts. Does not set advertising or analytics cookies on isov8.co.uk.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 align-top">
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Regulators, law enforcement, professional advisers</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Independent recipients</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">United Kingdom</td>
            <td class="break-words px-3 py-3">Disclosed only where required by law, to defend our legal rights, or to take legal advice.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      All processors act on our written instructions under contracts that meet the requirements of UK GDPR Article 28.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="international-transfers" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">5. International transfers</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      Some of the providers listed in section&nbsp;4 process personal data outside the United Kingdom &mdash; principally in the United States. Where personal data is transferred outside the UK, we rely on appropriate safeguards recognised under UK data protection law, such as the UK International Data Transfer Agreement, the UK Addendum to the EU Standard Contractual Clauses, or adequacy regulations made by the UK Government (including the UK Extension to the EU&ndash;US Data Privacy Framework where the recipient is certified).
    </p>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      You can ask us for a copy of the relevant safeguards using the contact details in section&nbsp;11.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="how-long" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">6. How long we keep your personal data</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We keep enquiry data (the information submitted through the Engage form, plus any related correspondence) for up to <strong>12&nbsp;months</strong> from the date of your last contact with us, after which it is deleted from our active systems. Where an enquiry leads to a contract or commercial relationship, the related personal data is retained for the duration of that relationship and afterwards in line with our statutory and tax obligations.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      Backup copies held by our processors may persist for a short period beyond active deletion in line with their standard backup cycles, after which they are overwritten. Cookie-related retention is set out in the <a href="/cookie-policy" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">Cookie Policy</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We may retain personal data for longer where we are required to by law, or where it is necessary to establish, exercise, or defend a legal claim.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="your-rights" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">7. Your rights</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      Under UK GDPR you have the following rights in relation to your personal data:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      <li><strong>Right of access</strong> &mdash; ask for a copy of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> &mdash; ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> &mdash; ask us to delete your personal data where one of the grounds in Article&nbsp;17 applies.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to restrict processing</strong> &mdash; ask us to pause processing while a query is resolved.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> &mdash; receive the data you provided in a structured, commonly used, machine-readable format, where the processing is based on consent or on a contract.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to object</strong> &mdash; object to processing carried out on the basis of our legitimate interests.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent</strong> &mdash; where processing is based on consent (including analytics cookies), you can withdraw your consent at any time. Withdrawal does not affect the lawfulness of processing carried out before withdrawal.</li>
      <li><strong>Rights in relation to automated decision-making</strong> &mdash; we do not use automated decision-making or profiling that produces legal or similarly significant effects.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      To exercise any of these rights, contact us using the details in section&nbsp;11. We will respond within one calendar month. We may need to verify your identity before acting on a request to make sure we do not disclose data to the wrong person.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="cookies" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">8. Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      The cookies and similar technologies used on isov8.co.uk are described in detail in our <a href="/cookie-policy" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">Cookie Policy</a>. Strictly necessary cookies are set automatically; analytics cookies (Google Analytics 4) are only used after you grant consent through the cookie banner. You can change or withdraw your consent at any time using the <em>Cookie Settings</em> link in the site footer.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="security-and-limits" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">9. Security, children, and what we do not do</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We take appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect personal data against unauthorised access, loss, or alteration. These include HTTPS/TLS encryption in transit, a strict Content Security Policy, access controls on our inboxes and processor accounts, and limiting access to enquiry data to staff who need it.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      The website is intended for business users and is not directed at children. We do not knowingly collect personal data from anyone under 16. If you believe a child has submitted personal data through the site, please contact us using the details in section&nbsp;11 and we will delete it.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We do not sell personal data; we do not share personal data with third parties for their own marketing purposes; we do not run a newsletter, mailing list, or marketing-follow-up programme; we do not build advertising audiences, retargeting audiences, or lookalike audiences; and we do not use automated decision-making or profiling that produces legal or similarly significant effects.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="ico-complaints" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">10. Right to complain to the ICO</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      If you are not satisfied with how we handle your personal data, we would like the chance to put it right &mdash; please contact us first using the details in section&nbsp;11. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the UK supervisory authority, the Information Commissioner&rsquo;s Office (ICO).
    </p>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      Information Commissioner&rsquo;s Office<br />
      Wycliffe House, Water Lane, Wilmslow, Cheshire, SK9 5AF<br />
      Helpline: <a href="tel:+443031231113" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">0303 123 1113</a><br />
      Website: <a href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint</a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="changes-to-policy" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">11. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in how we operate, the technology we use, or the law. The &ldquo;Published&rdquo; date at the foot of this page indicates when it was most recently revised. Where a change is material, we will draw it to your attention before it takes effect.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 space-y-3">
    <h2 id="contact-us" class="scroll-mt-36 text-[2.25rem] font-[600] leading-tight text-black">12. Contact us</h2>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, want to exercise any of your rights, or want a copy of the safeguards we use for international transfers, please contact us:
    </p>
    <p class="text-[1.125rem] leading-[1.8] text-[#4b5563]">
      ISOv8&reg; by ContainerKing&reg; Limited<br />
      Celsius Parc, Cupola Way, Scunthorpe, North Lincolnshire, United Kingdom, DN15 9YJ<br />
      Tel: <a href="tel:+441724870000" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">01724 870000</a><br />
      Email: <a href="mailto:engage@isov8.co.uk" class="text-[#088cbc] underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80">engage@isov8.co.uk</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</LegalPageLayout>
